    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Azure growth slows as data center shortages limit AI expansion</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-jan-30-1.png" alt="Azure growth slows as data center shortages limit AI expansion" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Microsoft provided a tepid outlook for cloud growth for the third quarter of the fiscal year, which led to a 5% decline in stock. The company’s cloud division, Azure, faces a lower-than-expected growth outlook as Microsoft faces <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-30-01-2025-h1-1-capacity-constraint-issues" target="_blank">capacity constraints issues</a> for data centers. The demand for cloud remains strong. However, the company cannot keep pace with the demand by expanding its infrastructure. Microsoft has around $300 billion in commercial contracts yet to be recognized as revenues. CFO Amy Hood expects the capacity limitations to ease off by the end of the fiscal year. For the fiscal quarter ending Dec. 31, Microsoft reported a 12% revenue increase to $69.6 billion and $3.23 per share profits.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Meta bets big on AI despite weak sales forecast and political shifts</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;filter:blur(5px);">Meta reported <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-30-01-2025-h2-2-fourth-quarter-earning" target="_blank">fourth-quarter earnings</a> with revenues of $48.4 billion, exceeding analysts' expectations. However, the company’s weak forecast for sales next quarter made Wall Street anxious, with the shares experiencing high volatility throughout the trading day. The company expects next quarter’s revenues to be between $ 39.5 billion to $41.8 billion. Zuckerberg expects the following year to be transformative for the company’s artificial intelligence efforts. The company continues to invest heavily in AI, with plans to spend as much as $65 billion in 2025 on AI infrastructure and its core business. The stock closed up 0.32% after fluctuating throughout the day.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
